    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received October 31.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson asks whether he is authorized to protect American merchandise
                        placed on Brazilian barges against the insurgents, using force if necessary.
                        He explains that cargoes can not be landed in Rio de Janeiro unless barges
                        are used.</p>
            </div>
